# DeLaw — Canonical Identifiers

Spec §3.2 inline comments DISAGREE with the §3.3 enum table in places.
**§3.3 is authoritative.** Use the values below verbatim.

## Enums (authoritative — §3.3)
- `org_type`: LAW_FIRM, CHAMBERS, CORPORATE, JUDICIARY, SOLO
- `user_role`: PARTNER, SENIOR_ASSOCIATE, ASSOCIATE, PARALEGAL, ADMIN, BILLING, CLIENT, JUDGE
- `subscription_plan`: FREE, SOLO, PROFESSIONAL, FIRM, ENTERPRISE
- `plan_status`: ACTIVE, TRIALING, PAST_DUE, CANCELLED, EXPIRED
- `matter_type`: LITIGATION, ADVISORY, TRANSACTION, COMPLIANCE, ARBITRATION
- `matter_status`: OPEN, IN_COURT, NEGOTIATION, SETTLEMENT, CLOSED, ARCHIVED
- `billing_type`: HOURLY, FIXED, CONTINGENCY, RETAINER, PRO_BONO
- `doc_type`: PLEADING, CONTRACT, BRIEF, MEMO, TEMPLATE, RESEARCH, GENERATED, UPLOADED
- `doc_status`: DRAFT, REVIEW, FINAL, ARCHIVED
- `content_type`: CASE_LAW, STATUTE, REGULATION, COURT_RULE, TREATY, PRACTICE_DIRECTION
- `invoice_status`: DRAFT, SENT, PAID, OVERDUE, CANCELLED
- `task_status`: TODO, IN_PROGRESS, REVIEW, DONE, CANCELLED
- `task_priority`: LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, URGENT
- `client_type`: INDIVIDUAL, CORPORATE
- `event_type`: HEARING, FILING, ADJOURNMENT, DEADLINE, JUDGMENT, NOTE

Free-text (NOT enums, store as TEXT): `research_sessions.mode` (QUICK|DEEP|CASE_LAW),
`matter_team.role` (LEAD|MEMBER|OBSERVER), `workflows.trigger_type`,
`ai_chat_messages.role` (user|assistant), `legal_content.authority_status`
(GOOD_LAW|OVERRULED|DISTINGUISHED|DOUBTED, default GOOD_LAW).

## Tables (British spelling: organisation, summarise)
organisations, users, matters, matter_team, documents, folders, clients,
legal_content, research_sessions, time_entries, invoices, tasks, matter_events,
ai_chat_sessions, ai_chat_messages, workflows, subscriptions, audit_logs.
Embedding columns are `VECTOR(1536)` on `documents` and `legal_content`.

## Route prefixes
- Node API public: `/api/v1/` — groups: auth, matters, documents, folders, users,
  clients, time-entries, invoices, payments, tasks, workflows, notifications,
  subscriptions, admin, search, ai.
- AI proxy (Node): `/api/v1/ai/{research, research/search, citation-check,
  proofread, summarise, draft, analyse-contract, chat, chat/sessions}`.
- Python AI internal (never public): `/internal/{research, search, citation-check,
  proofread, summarise, draft, analyse-contract, chat, embed, ingest}`.

## AI credit costs (§10.2)
research Quick=3, research Deep=8, contract analysis=10, draft=5,
proofread=2/1000 words, summarise=3, chat message=1, citation check=1.

## Design tokens (Tailwind, §14.3)
navy #0A0F1E, charcoal #111827, surface #1C2333 (raised #252B3E),
gold #C9A84C (hover #D4B563, muted #8B7340), border #2D3748 (hover #3D4A5C),
text primary #F0F4FF / secondary #8B95A8 / muted #4A5568.
